 {
 "cell_type": "markdown",
 "metadata": {},
 "source": [
  "**Finding: this dataset does not follow the 80/20 rule.** Revenue is spread almost evenly\n",
  "across the 25 items in the catalog \u2014 the top 20% of items (5 items) generate only ~22% of\n",
  "revenue, and it takes 80% of the catalog (20 of 25 items) to reach 80% of revenue. Individual\n",
  "items range narrowly from roughly $9.4K to $10.4K in total revenue, so there's no small \"vital\n",
  "few\" driving the business. At the category level there's a mild skew (Clothing \u2248 45% of\n",
  "revenue vs. an even 25% baseline across 4 categories), but that's a plurality, not\n",
  "Pareto-level concentration. **Business implication:** a \"focus on the top few SKUs\" inventory\n",
  "or marketing strategy isn't supported by this data \u2014 demand is broad-based, so category-level\n",
  "(not SKU-level) prioritization is the more defensible lever here."
 ],
 "id": "pareto-md-0002"
